Today is the day Aragon passed in 2020. 20 days later, Grandpa would join him. And 43 days after that, Grandma. Three within 63 days. 

That three number has stuck with me ever since. Three family members, three separate months, in a 63-day period. 

Three years without you three. I would REALLY love a shot right now, but I am trying to be better at that. Today marks 50 days & 165/216 days Wisco sober.  I think you'll understand. 

So to anyone who got through all that: Come have a shot of Jack Honey for Aragon if you could. I'd really appreciate it. 🙏  Cheers.

Thank you @martinirossius & @milliesmartinis for the mimosas & class yesterday! Had a blast!

I walked into my shift at High Fives in Dallas, Texas today & this was here waiting. I had no idea this was going on & they have never met Petey. Service Industry takes care of Service industry. I can't even describe how full my heart is. Being so far away from home right now has me in a mixed bag of emotions but Chandler, Corey, Kayla, & so many more people have shown me so much love, kindness, & patience these last few days that I will be forever grateful for. Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

San Antonio & Dallas are officially in the books. Stay tuned for a shit ton of amazing content from the week & then some! Thank you again, Chandler, all of our Heard house sponsors, & my hometown bars Pub On Wisconsin, The Void, & Olde Mke Pub for giving me the opportunity to represent Wisconsin right! I love you all!
